{{Infobox language family |name=Lenduic |region=[[Democratic Republic of Congo]] |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic]] |fam3=Eastern |child1=[[Lendu language|Lendu]] (Balendru) |child2=[[Ngiti language|Ngiti]] |child3=[[Ndrulo language|Ndrulo]] |glotto=lend1246 |glottorefname=Lenduic }}
The '''Lenduic languages''' of the [[Central Sudanic languages|Central Sudanic language family]] are a cluster of closely related languages spoken in the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]], and slightly over the border into [[Uganda]].
The languages are [[Lendu language|Lendu]] (Balendru), with over a million speakers, and the smaller [[Ngiti language|Ngiti]] and [[Ndrulo language|Ndrulo]], as well as perhaps an additional language or two among the 'dialects' o Balendru.
