{{infobox ethnonym||Bàgbɔ̀|Tɛ̀gbɔ̀||Tafi}}

The '''Nyangbo-Tafi''' language is spoken in the [[Volta Region]] of [[Ghana]]. It is considered one of the [[Ghana–Togo Mountain languages]] of the [[Kwa languages|Kwa family]].

It consists of two distinct varieties which ''Ethnologue'' treats as separate languages, Nyangbo (''Tutrugbu'') and Tafi (''Tegbo''). The differences are reported to be only phonological.

